            "Machine Learning is a foundational AI technology.\n\n**Definition:** ML enables systems to learn from data without explicit programming. System learns patterns and makes predictions.\n\n**Three Main Types:**\n\n1. **Supervised Learning:**\n   - Learning with labeled data\n   - Each data point has input and target output\n   - Regression: Predict continuous values (house price)\n   - Classification: Predict categories (spam or not)\n   - Algorithms: Linear Regression, Decision Trees, Random Forests, SVM\n   - Applications: Medical diagnosis, spam detection, price prediction\n\n2. **Unsupervised Learning:**\n   - Learning with unlabeled data\n   - Discover hidden patterns\n   - Clustering: Group similar items (customer segmentation)\n   - Dimensionality Reduction: Reduce features (PCA, t-SNE)\n   - Anomaly Detection: Find unusual patterns\n   - Applications: Customer segmentation, document clustering, fraud detection\n\n3. **Reinforcement Learning:**\n   - Learning through interaction and rewards\n   - Agent learns by trial and error\n   - Gets rewards for good actions, penalties for bad\n   - Algorithms: Q-Learning, Policy Gradient, DQN\n   - Applications: Game playing, robotics, autonomous vehicles\n\n**ML Workflow:**\n1. Problem Definition\n2. Data Collection\n3. Data Exploration\n4. Feature Engineering (crucial!)\n5. Data Preprocessing\n6. Train-Test Split\n7. Model Selection\n8. Model Training\n9. Model Evaluation\n10. Hyperparameter Tuning\n11. Deployment\n12. Monitoring & Maintenance\n\n**Evaluation Metrics:**\n\nRegression:\n- MAE: Mean Absolute Error\n- MSE: Mean Squared Error\n- RMSE: Root Mean Squared Error\n- R²: Proportion of variance explained\n\nClassification:\n- Accuracy: % correct\n- Precision: Of positive predictions, how many correct?\n- Recall: Of actual positives, how many found?\n- F1-Score: Balance of precision/recall\n- ROC-AUC: Area under ROC curve\n\n**Common Pitfalls:**\n1. Overfitting: Model learns training data too well\n2. Underfitting: Model too simple\n3. Data leakage: Test info leaks to training\n4. Class imbalance: One class much larger\n5. Feature scaling: Different feature ranges\n\n**Tools & Libraries (2026):**\n- scikit-learn: Most popular, beginner-friendly\n- TensorFlow: Deep learning\n- PyTorch: Deep learning, flexible\n- XGBoost: Extreme gradient boosting\n- Pandas: Data manipulation\n- NumPy: Numerical computing\n\n**Real-World Applications:**\n- Medical diagnosis\n- Fraud detection\n- Recommendations (Netflix, Amazon)\n- Self-driving cars\n- Stock prediction\n- Image recognition\n- NLP_Recognition tasks\n- Credit scoring"
