            "Image Recognition is a fundamental Computer Vision task.\n\n**Definition:** Image Recognition identifies and classifies objects, patterns, and features in images.\n\n**Tasks:**\n1. **Image Classification:** Assign category to entire image\n   - Example: Is this a cat or dog?\n   - Algorithms: CNNs (AlexNet, VGG, ResNet, MobileNet)\n\n2. **Object Detection:** Identify and locate objects\n   - Example: Find all people in image with bounding boxes\n   - Algorithms: YOLO, R-CNN, Faster R-CNN, SSD\n\n3. **Semantic Segmentation:** Classify each pixel\n   - Example: Which pixels are person, car, road?\n   - Algorithms: FCN, U-Net, DeepLab\n\n4. **Instance Segmentation:** Distinguish individual objects\n   - Example: Identify each person separately\n   - Algorithms: Mask R-CNN\n\n5. **Facial Recognition:** Identify people by faces\n   - Used in security, unlocking phones\n   - Algorithms: FaceNet, ArcFace\n\n**How It Works:**\n1. **Image Input:** Digital image (pixel array)\n2. **Feature Extraction:** CNN learns visual features\n   - Early layers: Edge, texture detection\n   - Middle layers: Shape, pattern recognition\n   - Deep layers: High-level features\n3. **Classification:** Fully connected layers classify\n4. **Output:** Class predictions or locations\n\n**Popular Architectures:**\n- **LeNet (1998):** First CNN, handwritten digits\n- **AlexNet (2012):** Breakthrough in ImageNet\n- **VGG:** Simple, effective design\n- **ResNet:** Very deep (150+ layers), skip connections\n- **Inception:** Efficient, multi-scale features\n- **MobileNet:** Lightweight, mobile devices\n- **EfficientNet:** Balance accuracy and efficiency\n- **Vision Transformer:** Transformer architecture for images\n\n**Challenges:**\n- Lighting and shadows\n- Occlusion: Objects partially hidden\n- Scale variation: Objects different sizes\n- Pose variation: Different angles\n- Background clutter\n- Real-time performance needs\n- Limited labeled training data\n\n**Applications (2026):**\n1. **Medical Imaging:** Detect tumors, fractures, abnormalities\n2. **Autonomous Vehicles:** Detect pedestrians, traffic signs, lanes\n3. **Facial Recognition:** Security, surveillance, phone unlock\n4. **Retail:** Cashier-less stores, inventory tracking\n5. **Manufacturing:** Quality control, defect detection\n6. **Agriculture:** Crop disease detection, harvest automation\n7. **Social Media:** Image classification, content moderation\n8. **Security:** Intruder detection, suspicious activity\n9. **Sports:** Player tracking, action recognition\n10. **Environmental:** Wildlife monitoring, climate tracking\n\n**Datasets (Training):**\n- ImageNet: 14M images, 1000 classes\n- COCO: Objects in context, 330K images\n- Pascal VOC: Detection and segmentation\n- CIFAR-10: Small images, 10 classes\n- Fashion-MNIST: Clothing items\n\n**Frameworks (2026):**\n- TensorFlow/Keras: Complete solution\n- PyTorch: Research and production\n- OpenCV: Image processing\n- MediaPipe: Ready-to-use models\n- ONNX: Model interoperability\n\n**Performance (2026):**\n- ImageNet accuracy: 99%+ with modern models\n- Real-time detection: 30+ FPS on GPU\n- Mobile inference: Fast on smartphones\n\n**Trends:**\n- Efficient architectures\n- Few-shot learning\n- Self-supervised learning\n- 3D vision and depth\n- Multimodal learning (vision + language)"
